FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1777683790
OL,3,CTree surgeon thought he was 'going to
OL,4,Cdie' during powerline electric shock
OL,6,F"Overhead electrical power lines
OL,7,Fpresent extreme risks to workers, but
OL,8,Fthe risks can and must be controlled.
OL,10,F"Work near overhead power lines should
OL,11,Fonly be carried out where it can be
OL,12,Fdone safely, following a suitable risk
OL,13,Fassessment, the use of barriers or
OL,14,Fsafety zones, and proper training on
OL,15,Fthe equipment being used.
OL,17,F"In this case, a worker sustained
OL,18,Fsevere injuries in a traumatic
OL,19,Fincident for all concerned that was
OL,20,Fentirely preventable.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
